#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:12
msgid "Boolean built-in type."
msgstr "布尔内置类型。"

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:15
msgid "Description"
msgstr "说明"

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:17
msgid ""
"Boolean is a built-in type. It can represent any data type that is either"
" a true or false value. You can think of it as an switch with on or off "
"(1 or 0) setting. It's often used as part of programming logic in "
"condition statements like ``if`` statements."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:19
msgid ""
"**Note:** In a code below ``if can_shoot`` is equivalent of ``if "
"can_shoot == true``. It is good practice to follow the natural spoken "
"language structure when possible. Use ``if can_shoot`` rather than ``if "
"can_shoot == true`` and use ``if not can_shoot`` rather than ``if "
"can_shoot == false``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:29
msgid ""
"The following code will only create a bullet if both conditions are met: "
"action \"shoot\" is pressed and if ``can_shoot`` is ``true``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:31
msgid ""
"**Note:** ``Input.is_action_pressed(\"shoot\")`` is also a boolean that "
"is ``true`` when \"shoot\" is pressed and ``false`` when \"shoot\" isn't "
"pressed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/classes/class_bool.rst:41
msgid ""
"The following code will set ``can_shoot`` to ``false`` and start a timer."
" This will prevent player from shooting until the timer runs out. Next "
"``can_shoot`` will be set to ``true`` again allowing player to shoot once"
" again."
msgstr ""

